slides.title: 3. Components of The Male Reproductive System
8. Sustentacular Cells and The Blood-Testis Barrier

interactions.lmstext: Choose one INCORRECT statement regarding the blood-testis barrier.

choices.lmstext: It controls the composition of the cytoplasm of sustentacular (Sertoli) cells.
It separates the basal from the adluminal comparments.
Structurally, it consists of tight junctions between adjacent sustentacular cells.
It shields maturing sperm from the immune system.

interactions.lmstext: Choose one INCORRECT statement regarding spermatogenesis.

choices.lmstext: Spermatogonia are haploid cells produced only after puberty.
The blood-testis barrier protects maturing sperm from detection by the immune system.
The most immature spermatogenic cells of the seminiferous tubule epithelium are adjacent to the basement membrane.
Mitotic divisions that occur at the beginning of spermatogenesis maintain the stem cell population.
